reviews.comment:
Unsure of how to charge with us? 

Check out the image that we’ve posted in the photo section for this location that outlines the steps to take to charge at an Electrify America DC Fast Charger. Following these steps, in this order, will help ensure a smooth session:

1. PLUG   2. PAY   3. CHARGE   4. GO

If you have any additional questions, please contact us at 833-632-2778 for assistance or check out the FAQs on our website at www.electrifyamerica.com/faqs

user.about:
Want to rent or test drive a 2018 Nissan Leaf SL with ProPilot?  Next time you’re in the DFW area you can rent mine.  Just go to Turo.com and search for a Nissan Leaf in the 76137 zip code.

I am a long advocate of sustainability.  I believe our freedoms are reflected in our freedom to travel.  My electric cars have given me a guilt free sense of transportation freedom that I have felt with no other mode of transportation.

reviews.comment: In cooperation with Huber+Suhner and our charger manufacturers, a thorough investigation was conducted into the potential safety concern with the high powered liquid cooled cables that are utilized at this Electrify America location. It was determined that the cables equipped on the CCS chargers at this location meet every standard for use and have been re-enabled. The safety of our customers is our top priority and we appreciate patience as we’ve taken these precautionary measures to complete the investigation. Additional information can be found at www.electrifyamerica.com/news-updates.

reviews.comment: Electrify America was recently informed of a potential safety concern by the supplier of a high powered cable used at some of the chargers at this location. The safety of our customers is our top priority. In an abundance of caution, the 150kW and 350kW CCS chargers at this location that are equipped with this cable have been disabled while the concern is investigated. The potential concern only affects chargers equipped with this cable and does not include any of the 50kW chargers or CHAdeMO units at the station. We will update this post when more information is available. More information can be found on our website at www.electrifyamerica.com/news-updates.

reviews.comment: Payments working now! One station offline.

I tried multiple stations withEA rep on the phone. After finay getting a charge to start it immediately stopped and my vehicle threw an error saying DC fast Charging not available. I have  $250 in card authorizations and two $1 session fees and got no charge.
Seems to be having an issue processing payments. They said they’re sending maintenance to fix it this week.
They are sending out maintenance for them.

If this location is anything like the one they opened up in Lafayette, IN, be prepared for multiple stations not working, start/stop issues, and soft resets from customer service. EA is very responsive when you call, but until they get the kinks worked out, don’t expect to get a fast charge in a hurry at these stations.

We are excited to be live in the market with our first few Electrify America LLC stations. During these initial deployments, some of our dispensers may experience an intermittent issue rendering them temporarily unavailable. Dispensers at this location may be affected and Electrify America is working to address this issue. If you are unable to initiate a charge at a particular dispenser, please contact us at 833-632-2778 for assistance.
